1. THE APLICATION
Pinna AR (“Licensed Application”) is a piece if software created to help hard of hearing users with
their day-to-day activities – and customized for iOS and Android mobile devices (“Devices”). It is
used for generating speech-to-text in real time.
The Licensed Application is not tailored to comply with industry-specific regulations (Health
Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA), Federal Information Security Management Act
(FISMA), etc.), so if your interactions would be subjected to such laws, you may not use this Licensed
Application. You may not use the Licensed Application in a way that would violate the Gramm-leach-
Bliley Act (GLBA).
